Brazilian Stock Movers: Brasil Foods, Pao de Acucar, Petrobras

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-05-25T20:29:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/brazilian-stock-movers-brasil-foods-pao-de-acucar-petrobras.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 0.1 percent to 63,388.44.  BRF Brasil Foods SA (BRFS3 BS) gained 1.4 percent to 29.50
reais. The world’s biggest poultry exporter offered to buy a
dairy unit from Industria de Alimentos Nilza for about 60
million reais ($37 million), newspaper O Estado de S. Paulo
reported, citing vice president of corporate affairs Wilson de Mello Neto.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar (PCAR4
BS) slid 0.5 percent to 65.67 reais. Brazil’s biggest retailer
said in a regulatory filing it isn’t in talks with Carrefour SA.
France’s Journal du Dimanche reported May 23 Carrefour was
planning a merger between its Brazilian unit and Pao de Acucar.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) gained 0.2 percent to
23.90 reais. Brazil’s state-controlled oil company may sell more
debt this year after issuing $6 billion of dollar-denominated
bonds in January, Chief Executive Officer Jose Sergio Gabrielli
said. Petrobras is considering its financing options as it
reviews 680 investment projects, Gabrielli said in an interview
today.  Tele Norte Leste Participacoes SA (TNLP3)  (TNLP4 BS) dropped 3.4
percent to 28.88 reais,  Brasil Telecom SA (BRTO4)  (BRTO4 BS) declined
2.8 percent to 16.30 reais, and  Telemar Norte Leste SA (TMAR5)  (TMAR5
BS) fell 3.8 percent to 58.41 reais. The stocks jumped the most
in over two years yesterday after parent company Telemar
Participacoes SA said it will merge the three units into one
entity named Oi SA, which will be  Brazil ’s largest fixed-line
telephone service provider.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
